<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78897705-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s207"><num value="207">§ 207.</num><heading> Preparation of standards by Secretary of Commerce</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Commerce is authorized and required to prepare suitable standards in accordance with <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s206">section 206 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78897706-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/act/1893-03-03/ch221/s2">Mar. 3, 1893, ch. 221, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/27/746">27 Stat. 746</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1903-02-14/ch552/s10">Feb. 14, 1903, ch. 552, § 10</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/32/829">32 Stat. 829</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1913-03-04/ch141/s1">Mar. 4, 1913, ch. 141, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/37/736">37 Stat. 736</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id78897707-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id78897708-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I78" topic="changeOfName" id="id78897709-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Change of Name</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Act <date date="1913-03-04">Mar. 4, 1913</date>, created Department of Labor, and renamed Department of Commerce and Labor as Department of Commerce.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I85" topic="transferOfFunctions" id="id7889770a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Transfer of Functions</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Act <date date="1903-02-14">Feb. 14, 1903</date>, transferred National Bureau of Standards from Treasury Department to Department of Commerce and Labor.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
